org.hibernate.loader.spi

Interface JoinableAssociation

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractJoinableAssociationImpl, CollectionJoinableAssociationImpl, EntityJoinableAssociationImpl

    public interface JoinableAssociation
    Represents a joinable (entity or collection) association.

      • getCurrentEntityReference

        EntityReference getCurrentEntityReference()
        Return the current EntityReference, or null if none.

        If getCurrentFetch() returns an EntityFetch, this method will return the same object as getCurrentFetch().

        If getCurrentFetch() returns a CollectionFetch and the collection's owner is returned or fetched, this method will return the EntityReference that owns the Fetch returned by getCurrentFetch(); otherwise this method returns null.

        Returns:
        the current EntityReference, or null if none.
        See Also:
        getCurrentFetch(), Fetch, CollectionFetch, EntityFetch, EntityReference

      • getCurrentCollectionReference

        CollectionReference getCurrentCollectionReference()
        Return the current CollectionReference, or null if none.

        If getCurrentFetch() returns a CollectionFetch, this method will return the same object as getCurrentFetch().

        If getCurrentFetch() returns an EntityFetch that is a collection element (or part of a composite collection element), and that collection is being returned or fetched, this method will return the CollectionReference; otherwise this method returns null.

        Returns:
        the current CollectionReference, or null if none.
        See Also:
        getCurrentFetch(), Fetch, EntityFetch, CollectionFetch, CollectionReference
